<br>
Start a petition.<br>
<br>
A couple weeks ago there was a thread started on a popular shaman board (the Crucible) petitioning to Verant that shaman 55+ spell-drops be upped. It got publicized through several other class boards (Safehouse, Rangers Glade, etc) as well as being mentioned up on Mobhunter. It ended up growing into a 500+ post, over 2k view thread. <br>
<br>
Two patches or so later what did the shamans  get? You guessed it, 'several 55+ spell drop rates have been increased'<br>
<br>
Just a thought, I do hope you guys get this heard at least. It certainly is a viable problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufuloriancavestomper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FulorianCavestomper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/23/02 12:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=307.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Petition?</span><hr size=1> The spells in question (Torpor, Malo, Pox, ect) are all still way too rare, and I'm not sure if the drop rates were even increased at all, really. Also, there have been some, in fact this thread started out being a link TO a petition I believe. It was locked and ignored by verant. So that doesn't work. <p>Veteran Fulorian Cavestomper <BR>
