<br>
You could be right, only IF the offhand epic did not give you 55 dext to your base stats.  <br>
<br>
The offhand epic is one of the greatest weapons available (Pre-SoL) and I would think that with its dext bonus (mine is currently 190 BASE).  <br>
<br>
Given the choice of epics / willsapper / FB<br>
<br>
I would chose Willsapper + Offhand epic - that would make my dext 185 (buffed with either boon or shaman dext/FoS) - 250 I believe = more procs = more taunts = me gets a bashing. <br>
<br>
And on the Severilious issue, no I dont think it should be changed in the slightest.  We are one of the lucky classes that do not have to camp anything really for our epic.  We just go get the part and jobs a good un.<br>
<br>
The cleric epic involves camping (sometimes long camps too) for parts they need.  Some of the other classes involve killing the same mob over and over (i.e.Phingel - Wizard) in the hope that they get a chance of the rare drop.  A bottle neck has occured in the enchanter epic, in Neriak - as soon as its up its down again - crappy repop time, then there is the Shissar too.    <br>
<br>
Severilious is fine as he is, his drop/pop rate should not increase imho, I understand there are 2 sources for the green scale as it is, how many for the red scale 5? 6?.  The warrior epic is not hard at all, it is just massively awkward - i.e. Queen = not hard, her pull is awkward, PoA = not hard, just awkward to get to, PoF = awkward cos u gotta clear all the plane beforehand, Sev = awkward because as soon as he is up you gotta take him down.<br>
<br>
Damn guys, what you want to buy it from the Shady in EC for 20pp or something ? &lt;that was a rhetorical question/sarcastic&gt;<br>
<br>
And finally, given the right focus and communication you can actually complete your epic quite quickly.  I managed to complete mine from beginning to end in one month.<br>
<br>
Raluvin Shadowsteele<br>
Half-Elven Warlord of Quellious <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uraluvinssteele.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raluvin Ssteele</A> at: 3/26/02 8:02:33 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhagusbruichladdich.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hagus Bruichladdich</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 9:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=307.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.divinelegion.com/images/Hagus_256color.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Scale mess</span><hr size=1> &quot;The cleric epic involves camping (sometimes long camps too) for parts they need.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ragefire?  &quot;Exactly&quot; the same as Severilious.  Same approximate spawn time out in an open area where people want it dead the second it spawns.  Only notable difference is that Rage will drop it's piece &quot;every&quot; time, and Sev won't.<br>
<br>
&quot;A bottle neck has occured in the enchanter epic, in Neriak - <br>
as soon as its up its down again - crappy repop time&quot;<br>
<br>
Reworded:  A bottle neck has occured in the warrior epic, in Emerald Jungle - as soon as it's up it's down again - crappy repop time.<br>
<br>
I don't see how you could be for Serevilious remaining exactly the same, saying that he's fine the way he is, yet in the same post say that these other things, which are &quot;EXACTLY&quot; the same, are all horrible and against them.<br>
<br>
If you think Sev is good, it doesn't make any sense that you think those other things are bad.  If you think Sev is bad, it wouldn't make sense if you thought those other things were good.  They're all practically one in the same, except that there is no guarantee that the piece will drop with Sev... putting Sev just over the top in being worse than the other examples you gave.<br>
<br>
I fail to see your logic in this.  It doesn't make sense at all.  It defies common sense. <p>--Hagus Bruichladdich<BR>
